\{x_A,y_A,z_A\}
\mathbb{R}^3
A
v\in \mathbb{R}^3
 A(v)
a,b,c
v=ax_A+by_A+cz_A
\{x_A,y_A,z_A\}
a=x_A\circ  v,b=y_A\circ v,c=z_A \circ v
p,q\in \mathbb{R}^3
A(p)\circ A(q)=p \circ q
p = (x_A \circ p)\cdot x_A + (y_A\circ p)\cdot y_A + (z_A \circ p)\cdot z_A,
A(p) = \begin{pmatrix}x_A\circ p\\y_A\circ p\\z_A\circ p \end{pmatrix},
q
\begin{align} A(p)\circ A(q) &= (x_A\circ p)\cdot (x_A\circ q) + (y_A\circ p)\cdot(y_A\circ q) + (z_A\circ p)\cdot(z_A\circ q)\\ &= ((x_A\circ p)\cdot x_A)\circ q + ((y_A\circ p)\cdot y_A)\circ q + ((z_A\circ p)\cdot z_A)\circ q\\ &= ((x_A \circ p)\cdot x_A + (y_A\circ p)\cdot y_A + (z_A \circ p)\cdot z_A)\circ q\\ &= p\circ q \end{align}
